translation:
Of the Brahmin nature are serenity, self-control, austerity, cleanliness, contentment, forgiveness, honesty, and determination; of the Kshatriya nature are valor, strength, steadfastness, forbearance, and generosity;
of the Vaishya nature are piety, charity, reliability, modesty, and pursuit of wealth;
and of the Shudra nature is service to the three upper castes, with satisfaction arising from fulfilling one's duties.
